Right - the `pattern` argument gets passed to `pytest -k`, which filters by test *name*, not by file path. That's why all 153 tests got deselected. The tool needs a `file` attribute to pass a file path directly to pytest as a positional argument.

Let me add `file` support to the `run_tests` tool:

<edit file="forge/tools/builtin/run_tests.py">
<search>
# Pattern: <run_tests/> or <run_tests pattern="..." verbose="true"/>
_INLINE_PATTERN = re.compile(
    r'<run_tests(?:\s+pattern="([^"]*)")?(?:\s+verbose="(true|false)")?\s*/?>',
    re.DOTALL,
)
</search>
<replace>
# Pattern: <run_tests/> or <run_tests file="..." pattern="..." verbose="true"/>
_INLINE_PATTERN = re.compile(
    r'<run_tests(?:\s+file="([^"]*)")?(?:\s+pattern="([^"]*)")?(?:\s+verbose="(true|false)")?\s*/?>',
    re.DOTALL,
)
</replace>
</edit>

